  "prompt": "Does the files sent through share it have less resolution?",
  "response": "The files sent through ShareIt (or similar file-sharing apps) typically retain their original resolution and quality, as long as the app transfers the files without compressing them. ShareIt, particularly in its earlier versions, was known for transferring files directly from one device to another without altering their quality.\n\nHowever, there are a few factors to consider:\n\n1. **App Settings**: Some file-sharing apps may have options to compress files (e.g., images or videos) to speed up the transfer process. If compression is enabled, the resolution and quality of the files could be reduced.\n\n2. **Type of File**: For images and videos, the resolution and quality depend on the original file and whether the app modifies it during transfer. For other files, like documents or apps, the content remains unchanged.\n\n3. **App Version and Platform**: Different versions of ShareIt or other file-sharing apps may handle file transfers differently. Always check the settings to ensure files are transferred without compression.\n\n4. **Storage and Compatibility**: Some devices or operating systems may automatically compress media files when received, depending on their settings or storage constraints.\n\nTo ensure files retain their original resolution, verify the settings in the file-sharing app and ensure no compression is applied during the transfer. If you're concerned about quality, you can also use alternative methods like USB transfers or cloud services that preserve the original file properties.",
